I got to try @doghausdogs’ NEW KPOP Burger before it’s launched tomorrow and, I have to tell you... It’s maybe my favorite burger I’ve had all year 🍔 It's a Korean fusion burger created in collaboration with @chefchrisoh. 2 griddle-smashed wagyu beef patties covered in kalbi glaze and topped with white American cheese and KPOP 1000 Island sauce on a buttered & grilled King’s Hawaiian bun 🤤 It's only going to be available a limited time, so make sure you go try it before it's too late. Trust me... You don't want to miss this one. #dailyfoodfeed

As a foodie, people always ask me, “What’s the best thing you’ve ever eaten?” I feel like I disappoint people when I say an @innout burger 🍔 What those people don't know is there's history behind my answer. Growing up in a Filipino household, fast food was a luxury and a special treat. Culturally, we never really ate burgers and fries, let alone In-N-Out. The first time I had an In-N-Out burger was in Middle School when a friend's mom took us through the drive thu during a carpool home. I was embarrassed that I never had In-N-Out because my friends talked about it all the time. So I pretended like I had it before. I can still remember my first bite... and having to control losing it in front of my friend before he found out I’ve never really had it before. It just tasted so damn good. And it still tastes so damn good every time. It may not be the most sophisticated food, but it’s still one of the best things I ever ate. And I’m sticking to it. Stay hungry. Stay foolish.
❤️,
Jed @dailyfoodfeed
